  "ai_usage": "Playful decorative cursor companion (keep the real cursor visible for usability). Render a fixed blurred radial blob; store the pointer target on pointermove and lerp the blob toward it in a rAF loop (current += (target-current)*ease) using transform: translate. Lower ease = more lag/trail. Skip the animation under reduced motion and on touch. Keep blur moderate for perf.",
  "path": "effects/cursors-pointers/blob-trail-cursor.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Gooey Blob Trail Cursor</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"blob-trail-cursor\",\n    \"title\": \"Gooey Blob Trail Cursor\",\n    \"summary\": \"A soft blurred blob chases the cursor with easing, leaving a liquid trailing feel.\",\n    \"description\": \"A blurred radial blob is eased toward the pointer each frame (lerp), so it lags and stretches subtly — a playful, organic cursor companion.\",\n    \"theme\": \"cursors-pointers\",\n    \"categories\": [\"cursor\", \"pointer\", \"ambient\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"cursor\", \"blob\", \"trail\", \"gooey\", \"lerp\", \"blur\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\", \"js\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"intermediate\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"Pointer devices; modern browsers. No-ops on touch.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"One rAF loop moving a single blurred element via transform; cheap. Blur is the main cost — keep it moderate.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Decorative only; does NOT replace the system cursor here (kept visible), so usability is preserved. Stop the lag/motion under prefers-reduced-motion.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--blob\", \"description\": \"Blob color\", \"default\": \"#7c5cff\" },\n      { \"name\": \"ease\", \"description\": \"Follow lag (0-1)\", \"default\": \"0.12\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Color-shift the blob over time\", \"Scale the blob on click\", \"mix-blend-mode: difference over content\"],\n    \"related\": [\"follow-dot-cursor\", \"spotlight-cursor\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Playful decorative cursor companion (keep the real cursor visible for usability). Render a fixed blurred radial blob; store the pointer target on pointermove and lerp the blob toward it in a rAF loop (current += (target-current)*ease) using transform: translate. Lower ease = more lag/trail. Skip the animation under reduced motion and on touch. Keep blur moderate for perf.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root { --blob: #7c5cff; }\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; overflow: hidden; }\n    body { display: grid; place-items: center; background: #06060c; color: #8b93a7; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .blob {\n      position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 60px; height: 60px; border-radius: 50%; pointer-events: none; z-index: 5;\n      background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--blob), transparent 70%); filter: blur(8px); transform: translate(-50%,-50%);\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Move your cursor around</p>\n  <div class=\"blob\" id=\"blob\"></div>\n  <script>\n    var blob = document.getElementById(\"blob\");\n    var tx = innerWidth/2, ty = innerHeight/2, x = tx, y = ty;\n    var reduce = matchMedia(\"(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)\").matches;\n    addEventListener(\"pointermove\", function (e) { tx = e.clientX; ty = e.clientY; });\n    function frame() {\n      var ease = reduce ? 1 : 0.12;\n      x += (tx - x) * ease; y += (ty - y) * ease;\n      blob.style.transform = \"translate(\" + x + \"px,\" + y + \"px) translate(-50%,-50%)\";\n      requestAnimationFrame(frame);\n    }\n    frame();\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
